pan> Enjoy one last ride along the Danube to Spitz.',4),(1753611,777,'1-2','Les Alpilles, a world of windswept crags carpeted with oak, pine and cypress trees','<span class=\"divide\">|</span> Explore the ancient village of Les Baux, perched above the Val d\'Enfer (Valley of Hell), an eerie limestone landscape dotted with caves <span class=\"divide\">|</span> Quintessential Provence awaits in St-Rémy, an artists\' haven brimming with cafés and treelined boulevards <span class=\"divide\">|</span> Bike to Eygalières, a terraced town guarded by an ancient castle <span class=\"divide\">|</span> Spin to the walled village of Ménerbes, nestled in the romantic Luberon, beloved by writers and artists <span class=\"divide\">|</span> In Bonnieux, it\'s just 86 steps to the top of the town\'s church tower, where spectacular views stretch forever <span class=\"divide\">|</span> Vincent van Gogh painted the starry nights of Provence&mdash;you\'ll enjoy stars of the Michelin variety at our hotel\'s acclaimed restaurant. ',1),(1753612,777,'3-4','Fall in love with the Luberon','as you rub shoulders with the locals in heavenly Provençal villages like Lacoste and ocher-colored Roussillon <span class=\"divide\">|</span> Feel free to linger in Gordes, where labyrinthine lanes lead to shady squares and cafés, and a massive 12th-century castle keeps watch over the neighboring hilltop towns. ',2),(1753613,777,'5-6','Lose yourself amid vineyards and orchards','while pedaling to your heart\'s content in the lavender-scented countryside <span class=\"divide\">|</span> You\'ll feel like this peaceful pocket of Provence is your secret discovery! <span class=\"divide\">|</span> Ever tried goat cheese wrapped in chestnut leaves? Today\'s your chance in the town of Banon <span class=\"divide\">|</span> Explore the hilltop town of Simiane la Rotonde <span class=\"divide\">|</span> Indulging in a treatment at our hotel\'s lovely L\'Occitane spa is the ultimate way to add a flourish to the day <span class=\"divide\">|</span> Take aim during a rousing round of <em>pétanque</em> <span class=\"divide\">|</span> Head out on a final spin through the serene sun-drenched countryside. ',3),(1753673,2975,'1','The shady waterways, arched bridges, crooked canal houses and bohemian vibe of Amsterdam will delight you','<span class=\"divide\">|</span> Admire the picture-perfect town of Edam, home of the namesake cheese <span class=\"divide\">|</span> Iconic windmills and ubiquitous dikes set the stage for a truly Dutch ride. <i>(Overnight Amsterdam)</i>',1),(1753674,2975,'2','A picturesque spin through the serene Dutch countryside','leads to the medieval castle of Wijk <span class=\"divide\">|</span> Gaze at pastoral scenery from the Sun Deck this afternoon as we cruise on to our next adventure. <i>(Cruise afternoon/overnight Amsterdam to Cologne)</i>',2),(1753675,2975,'3','Cruise to Cologne for a leisurely cycling tour through the atmospheric <i>Altstadt</i> (old town)','<span class=\"divide\">|</span> Feel dwarfed by Cologne\'s Gothic cathedral, enjoy a sniff of authentic Eau de Cologne, visit a chocolate shop and sip coffee at a quaint café <span class=\"divide\">|</span> Or head out of town on your bike for a ride in the surrounding landscape <span class=\"divide\">|</span> Linger in beautiful Koblenz, a 2,000-year-old town famously set at the Deutsches Eck (German Corner), where the Rhine and Moselle Rivers converge. <i>(Overnight Koblenz)</i>',3),(1753676,2975,'4','Pedal past fairy-tale towns, castles and vineyards through the Rhine Gorge,','a World Heritage landscape <span class=\"divide\">|</span> A mouthwatering picnic at a local winery awaits, complete with a taste of riesling <span class=\"divide\">|</span> Meander the narrow cobblestone streets of riverside Rüdesheim. <i>(Cruise overnight Rüdesheim to Speyer)</i>',4),(1753677,2975,'5','Arrive by ship midday in Speyer, one of Germany\'s oldest cities,','acclaimed for its Romanesque cathedral and 13th-century Altpörtel (Old Gate) <span class=\"divide\">|</span> Point your wheels toward Schwetzingen Palace, with its ornate gardens and impressive mosque <span class=\"divide\">|</span> When the mood strikes: a local biergarten, a few new friends and a refreshing beer or Radler. <i>(Cruise overnight Speyer to Strasbourg)</i>',5),(1753678,2975,'6','Spin past Strasbourg\'s famed landmarks&mdash;the soaring Gothic cathedral with its popular astronomical clock,','Le Jardin de l\'Orangerie park and the European Parliament <span class=\"divide\">|</span> A landscape of rolling farmland and tidy orchards unfolds outside of this World Heritage city <span class=\"divide\">|</span> Stroll the historic streets of Strasbourg and experience the region\'s delicious French- and German-inspired cuisine. <i>(Overnight Strasbourg)</i>',6),(1753679,2975,'7-8','After a morning sail on the Rhine, superb riding and wine tasting await','along the famous Route des Vins in Alsace <span class=\"divide\">|</span> Bike through vineyards to some of the most beautiful villages in France, such as Riquewihr and Eguisheim, brimming with stunning Gothic churches, half-timbered houses and medieval fortifications. <i>(Cruise overnight Breisach to Basel)</i>',7),(1753683,593,'1-2','From the hamlet of Monticchiello,','discover the picture-perfect landscape of the Val d\'Orcia <span class=\"divide\">|</span> Have a look around Renaissance-style Pienza, Pope Pius II\'s utopian village, perhaps stopping to try the superb local pecorino cheese <span class=\"divide\">|</span> In springtime, the surrounding hills provide a backdrop of emerald green, while in the fall, hay bales turn the landscape a brilliant shade of gold <span class=\"divide\">|</span> Sample a variety of regional vintages from our hotel\'s premium cellar <span class=\"divide\">|</span> Follow a quiet route up to the majestic Castello di Brolio, where Baron Bettino Ricasoli formulated the modern method of producing Chianti Classico in the 19th century.',1),(1753684,593,'3-4','Explore the heart of the \"Land of the Black Rooster\"','<span class=\"divide\">|</span> From Radda, amble through pristine vineyards and pine forests in the center of Chianti Classico wine country <span class=\"divide\">|</span> You\'ll find that Siena, home to Italy\'s famous Il Palio horse race, is perfect for an evening stroll <span class=\"divide\">|</span> Take a break in Vertine\'s cozy <i>piazzetta</i> to enjoy a cappuccino and observe the friendly pace of local life <span class=\"divide\">|</span> In Panzano, learn about ancient recipes and the region\'s finest meats at Dario Cecchini\'s renowned <i>macelleria </i><span class=\"divide\">|</span> Stride along the crest to Montefioralle, birthplace of Amerigo Vespucci <span class=\"divide\">|</span> Savor Michelin-starred cuisine inspired by Tuscan traditions.',2),(1753685,593,'5-6','In the Colli Fiorentini (Florentine Hills),','vineyards and wildflower fields greet you at every turn <span class=\"divide\">|</span> Step back into history in the World Heritage site of San Gimignano, a magnificent village crowned by 12th- and 13th-century towers <span class=\"divide\">|</span> Hike hilly roads through oak forests and along ridges offering sweeping views that once inspired Renaissance artists.',3),(1754622,3026,'1-2','Get ready to view sand dunes, cinder cones and towering cliffs in Snow Canyon State Park','<span class=\"divide\">|</span> Hike along the canyon rim amid red and white Navajo sandstone and black lava rock, then descend into its depths <span class=\"divide\">|</span> Keep your eyes peeled for wildlife such as coyotes, roadrunners and quail <span class=\"divide\">|</span> Scramble on petrified dunes for superb views of ancient lava flows, serpentine washes and massive stone domes <span class=\"divide\">|</span> Follow part of the St. George Ironman route on your way to Gunlock State Park <span class=\"divide\">|</span> You can spot the rim of Zion Canyon from here!',1),(1754623,3026,'3','Journey to Zion National Park, taking in vistas of the Pine Valley Mountains along the way','<span class=\"divide\">|</span> The valley floor\'s sleepy towns and weathered farms add to the postcard-perfect scenery <span class=\"divide\">|</span> Get set for an exhilarating adventure in the Narrows&mdash;one of <em>Backpacker</em> magazine\'s Best Hikes Ever&mdash;a trek through the inner gorge of the Virgin River amid waterfalls, hanging gardens and sheer sandstone up to 1,000 feet high  <span class=\"divide\">|</span> With crimson cliffs and enormous monoliths soaring around you, it\'s only natural to be awestruck in Zion National Park!',2),(1754624,3026,'4-5','It\'s a thrilling hike to Angels Landing, bringing you nearly 1,500 feet above the valley','for a 360-degree panorama of soaring sandstone <span class=\"divide\">|</span> Or, if heights aren\'t your thing, you can experience the park\'s grandeur on a stunning hike through cottonwood, box elder and Gambel oak trees to Emerald Pools <span class=\"divide\">|</span> Soak it all in as you bike along car-free Zion Canyon Scenic Drive <span class=\"divide\">|</span> You\'ll pedal beside the Virgin River amid walls of steep rock rising 2,000 feet from the canyon floor&mdash;it\'s quiet, peaceful and absolutely breathtaking!',3),(1754809,3000,'1','Journey from Palm Springs to Joshua Tree National Park','<span class=\"divide\">|</span> Stop in at the visitor center for an intro to the park\'s geologic history and its plant and animal life, including the <i>Yucca brevifolia</i>&mdash;the famed Joshua trees <span class=\"divide\">|</span> Enjoy your first taste of the dramatic desert landscape with a brief walk and a fun downhill spin <span class=\"divide\">|</span> Marvel at geologic wonders in a box canyon.',1),(1754810,3000,'2','Sweeping views, vast skies and, of course, giant-sized boulders await at Joshua Tree\'s picturesque Jumbo Rocks ','<span class=\"divide\">|</span> Pedal past strange and wonderful rock formations and mile upon mile of Joshua trees <span class=\"divide\">|</span> Skull Rock&mdash;you\'ll know it when you see it <span class=\"divide\">|</span> Two-wheel it to Keys View for an amazing vista across the Coachella Valley.',2),(1754811,3000,'3','Ride to a hidden desert oasis, where year-round water sustains groves of California fan palms ','<span class=\"divide\">|</span> Keep an eye out&mdash;these stands of palms  are superb spots to watch for birds, including brightly colored orioles and hummingbirds <span class=\"divide\">|</span> Tonight\'s dinner in lively Palm Springs will seem worlds away from the quietude of Joshua Tree.',3),(1754812,3000,'4','No trip to the Palm Springs area is complete without a ride on the famous Aerial Tramway, ','featuring the world\'s largest rotating tram cars <span class=\"divide\">|</span> Sit back and enjoy breathtaking views of the Coachella Valley and the sheer cliffs of Chino Canyon as you ascend to the Mountain Station at 8,516 feet <span class=\"divide\">|</span> Be prepared for a big temperature change at this height&mdash;and possibly even snow&mdash;as you enjoy a short hike with stellar views around every bend.',4),(1755934,645,'1','Bike across the giant Salt Playa to the lowest point in the United States ','and see if you feel any different at 282 feet below sea level <span class=\"divide\">|</span> Desert illusions of water might just mesmerize you <span class=\"divide\">|</span> Opt for a round of golf or kick back and relax at the Inn at Furnace Creek, a natural oasis where 50 freshwater springs provide water for drinking, showers, irrigation and even the swimming pool. ',1),(1755935,645,'2','For an excellent introduction to the natural wonders','you\'ll experience during your trip, have a look around the Death Valley National Park Visitor Center <span class=\"divide\">|</span> Delight in the peacefulness of the desert as you set off on your first ride, highlighted by sights both grand and intimate&mdash;from immense sand dunes to salt-tolerant pickleweed.',2),(1755936,645,'3','Two-wheel it down the valley with views of the Panamint Mountains','and sand dunes in the distance <span class=\"divide\">|</span> Pay a visit to the eerie ghost town of Rhyolite, a once-prosperous town site teeming with prospectors and a mine owned by Charles Schwab <span class=\"divide\">|</span> Ascend to the highest peak of the trip&mdash;Daylight Pass.',3),(1755937,645,'4','Ascend to Zabriskie Point, the park\'s most celebrated vista','<span class=\"divide\">|</span> Take in the badlands\' yellow sandstone and ancient lava flows in the Black Mountains to the south <span class=\"divide\">|</span> Hike through out-of-this-world rock formations resembling Neapolitan ice cream <span class=\"divide\">|</span> Explore Golden Canyon, a slot canyon that you may recognize from the original <i>Star Wars</i> films.',4),(1756427,2966,'1-2','Discover Angkor as you pedal among iconic stone monuments,','learning about the Khmer civilizations <span class=\"divide\">|</span> Receive a water blessing from a monk <span class=\"divide\">|</span> Visit a market and an artisan\'s workshop <span class=\"divide\">|</span> Greet the sunrise over Angkor Wat <span class=\"divide\">|</span> Explore the Roluos Group, temples dating back to the 9th century and hailed as Angkor\'s oldest <span class=\"divide\">|</span> Have lunch in a local home.',1),(1756428,2966,'3','Travel from Siem Reap to the start of our Mekong River journey ','<span class=\"divide\">|</span> Get a first taste of the region\'s rustic river life <span class=\"divide\">|</span> Arrive in Kampong Chhnang aboard our luxury river ship.',2),(1756429,2966,'4-6','Bike along Tonlé Sap past mangroves and rich wildlife habitat','<span class=\"divide\">|</span> Exchange greetings with shy&mdash;but curious!&mdash;local kids <span class=\"divide\">|</span> Pedal into nearby hills to an ancient temple <span class=\"divide\">|</span> Sail to Phnom Penh and head into town to sample exotic cuisine <span class=\"divide\">|</span> Spin through the city\'s fascinating back alleys to Koh Dac island, known for its silkweaving <span class=\"divide\">|</span> On a guided walking tour of Phnom Penh, soak up French colonial architecture, lively cafés and colorful markets. ',3),(1756430,2966,'7-8','Cruise from Phnom Penh and pedal into Vietnam on a route lined with rice fields, gardens and old wooden bridges','<span class=\"divide\">|</span> Cycle and sail narrow waterways to an ecological reserve <span class=\"divide\">|</span> Admire fine handicrafts in silk- and rattan-making workshops <span class=\"divide\">|</span> This afternoon, enjoy the views from the Sun Deck as you cruise along the Mekong.',4),(1756431,2966,'9-10','On foot, witness the buzz of activity on the busy docks of Sa Dec,','home of the French writer Marguerite Duras <span class=\"divide\">|</span> Savor a final ride along the Mekong as it widens into a vast delta, arriving by bike and boat at Cai Be <span class=\"divide\">|</span> In the morning, journey to Ho Chi Minh City.',5),(1758200,667,'1-2','Stroll with our Kiwi guide past giant tree ferns and hanging vines','to a hidden pool in the Broken Hills wilderness <span class=\"divide\">|</span> Can you believe this forest has remained virtually unchanged for millions of years? <span class=\"divide\">|</span> Pedal to Hahei and kayak in Cathedral Cove, a little piece of heaven on earth with a white-sand beach, sculpted sandstone monoliths and gentle crystalline waters.',1),(1758201,667,'3','Traditional Maori customs and foods at a <i>marae</i>','(ceremonial meeting place) <img src=\"/_images/bullets/gold_star.gif\" width=\"10\" height=\"10\"> Hike the lush Karangahake Gorge, a historically rich gold-mining area, active for more than 75 years <img src=\"/_images/bullets/gold_star.gif\" width=\"10\" height=\"10\"> Venture across suspension bridges to a ridgetop affording gorgeous views <img src=\"/_images/bullets/gold_star.gif\" width=\"10\" height=\"10\"> Ready to cool down? Splash in the Waitawheta River. \n',2),(1758202,667,'4','Cycle along the waters of','Lake Rotoiti and into the Rotorua hills <span class=\"divide\">|</span> Along the way, explore quiet inlets and spot a variety of native birds <span class=\"divide\">|</span> Ever fed an emu or watched sheepshearers in action? Never say never!',3),(1758203,667,'5-7','Tame the Tongariro River on a Class III rafting trip','<span class=\"divide\">|</span> Pedal through rolling pastures of farmland and along the white cliffs of the Paeroa Range to Waikite Hot Pools, perfect for a dip <span class=\"divide\">|</span> Watch your step&mdash;geysers, thermal springs, colorful silica terraces and percolating mudpots abound at Waiotapu <span class=\"divide\">|</span> At Huka Falls, witness the Waikato River as it enters a narrow rock channel and emerges in a spectacular display of foam and spray <span class=\"divide\">|</span> Feeling fearless? Try a bungee jump over the river.',4),(1758223,2949,'1','Journey by traditional dugout canoe through the rain forest to an indigenous Emberá village','<span class=\"divide\">|</span> Learn about this community\'s culture and taste its cuisine <span class=\"divide\">|</span> Catch a glimpse of sloths, birds and monkeys on a hike through Parque Metropolitano, Panama City\'s only wildlife refuge <span class=\"divide\">|</span> Take a walking tour of Casco Viejo\'s historic plazas and cathedrals.',1),(1758224,2949,'3','Marvel at the Panama Canal, a 100-year-old engineering feat of epic proportions','<span class=\"divide\">|</span> Find out about the canal\'s historical significance, its construction and watershed during a private guided tour of the Miraflores Locks museum <span class=\"divide\">|</span> Take in the beauty of the Chagres River on a peaceful downstream paddle amid lush green vegetation and brilliant tropical birds <span class=\"divide\">|</span> Keep an eye out for toucans, monkeys and maybe even a kinkajou as you hike to Gamboa\'s observation tower, where you can see Soberanía National Park from above.',2),(1758225,2949,'4','Surrounded by rain forest, pedal from the Gatun Locks','to the haunting ruins of a Spanish fort dating back to the 16th century <span class=\"divide\">|</span> Search for capybaras (the world\'s largest rodent), caimans and turtles in one of the best-studied forests in the world <span class=\"divide\">|</span> Explore Fort San Lorenzo, a hidden jewel on the Caribbean coast <span class=\"divide\">|</span> Boat across the bay to our luxury boutique hotel <span class=\"divide\">|</span> Dine on International-Caribbean cuisine while admiring views of Portobelo Bay.',3),(1758226,2949,'5-6','Bike to the coast from Portobelo, a sleepy fishing village','that was once a vital stop in the Spanish silver trade route <span class=\"divide\">|</span> Set sail for a day of snorkeling, swimming and sunbathing on the sandy shores of Playa Blanca <span class=\"divide\">|</span> At our tropical retreat, the afternoon is yours to hike, fish or relax poolside <span class=\"divide\">|</span> Explore Spanish colonial fortifications, designated a World Heritage site. ',4),(1759508,572,'1','Find paradise among the flora and fauna of the rain forest and the grandeur of volcanic mountains','<span class=\"divide\">|</span> Connect with the friendly and welcoming Costa Rican <i>campesinos</i> on a countryside hike <span class=\"divide\">|</span> Settle in at our secluded hotel, tucked into the lush rain forest.',1),(1759509,572,'2','Discover Tenorio Volcano National Park, where monkeys, iguanas, sloths, butterflies and frogs are frequently spotted','<span class=\"divide\">|</span> Trek to Río Celeste and learn the secrets of its distinctive teal hue <span class=\"divide\">|</span> Come face-to-face with the jaw-dropping Celeste Waterfall, whose surreal beauty you have to see to believe <span class=\"divide\">|</span> Get a glimpse into a Tico 