|</span> Take a siesta on your private terrace or stretch your legs on a stroll along a white-sand beach <span class=\"divide\">|</span> Enjoy a traditional cooking class, learning about Mexican cuisine and Maya legends <span class=\"divide\">|</span> Optional on-your-own activities abound: kayak, paddleboard or treat yourself to a massage... scuba certified? This area is a mecca for divers! <span class=\"divide\">|</span> Celebrate a sensational week in Mexico with a dinner by the beach <span class=\"divide\">|</span> End your journey with an all-levels yoga class.',4),(1802329,3237,'1','','Adventure and serenity await in Utah&rsquo;s remote canyons where the relentless power of wind and water have shaped the landscape into something otherworldly <span class=\"divide\">|</span> Get to know Bryce Canyon as you take in extraordinary views from the rim then descend on foot into a labyrinth of delicate red-rock pillars called hoodoos <span class=\"divide\">|</span> Visit the Temple of Osiris, Queen Victoria and Thor&rsquo;s Hammer then take a stroll down Wall Street <span class=\"divide\">|</span> Relax at our hotel situated near the canyon rim.',1),(1802330,3237,'2','','Amble along the Fairyland Trail where every step brings new and impressive geological discoveries <span class=\"divide\">|</span> Learn about the Native American legend that led the Paiute people to call this land Angka-ku-wass-a-wits (Red Painted Faces) <span class=\"divide\">|</span> Take your cycling prowess to new heights as you pedal to 9,100-foot Rainbow Point <span class=\"divide\">|</span> Once the sun sets, Bryce&#39;s night sky offers incredible stargazing opportunities..',2),(1802331,3237,'3','','Coast along a paved bike path where stands of green ponderosa pines contrast with red sandstone pillars <span class=\"divide\">|</span> Sit back and enjoy the ride en route to Capitol Reef National Park along Utah&rsquo;s All-American Road, Scenic Byway 12 <span class=\"divide\">|</span> Pass through the once inaccessible town of Boulder, the last in the nation to receive mail by mule train <span class=\"divide\">|</span> A refreshing dip in the pool awaits at our hotel near the park&#39;s entrance.',3),(1802332,3237,'4-5','','Explore one of Utah&rsquo;s best-kept secrets, a place the Navajo called Land of the Sleeping Rainbow <span class=\"divide\">|</span> Venture toward the Waterpocket Fold, a mammoth buckling of the earth&rsquo;s surface almost 100 miles long <span class=\"divide\">|</span> Gaze over a landscape that looks much like it did when John Wesley Powell&rsquo;s famous expedition passed through in 1869 <span class=\"divide\">|</span> Hike amid rock formations resembling the rounded white dome of the US capitol building, in part the inspiration for the park&#39;s name <span class=\"divide\">|</span> Glimpse historical remains of the pre-Colombian Fremont culture and a thriving orchard planted by 19th-century Mormon pioneers <span class=\"divide\">|</span> Trek under and then across a picturesque 133-foot natural arch.',4),(1802373,3207,'1-2','','Start your adventure with a splash, kayaking and snorkeling among colorful tropical sea life in Maui\'s Olowalu Reef <span class=\"divide\">|</span> The island is surrounded by prime whale-watching waters from December through April&mdash;spot these magnificent creatures up close on an excursion from charming Lahaina <span class=\"divide\">|</span> Hike the Waihee Ridge Trail in the West Maui Mountains, one of Maui\'s best-kept secrets <span class=\"divide\">|</span> Optional on-your-own activities abound at the luxurious oceanfront Fairmont Kea Lani&mdash;relax by the pool, pamper yourself with a spa treatment, surf or stand-up paddleboard.',1),(1802374,3207,'3','','Enjoy scenic island views while riding through the rich volcanic farmland of the island\'s bucolic up-country <span class=\"divide\">|</span> Savor lunch and visit local artist shops in the laid-back surf town of Paia <span class=\"divide\">|</span> Discover the famed road to Hana on the island\'s eastern tip <span class=\"divide\">|</span> Winding and remote, the route follows 52 miles of unspoiled coastline <span class=\"divide\">|</span> Stop along the way to stretch your legs on a coastal walk and try the island\'s famous banana bread.',2),(1802375,3207,'4-5','','Visit Haleakala National Park and hike through some of Maui\'s most diverse scenery on the Pipiwai Trail <span class=\"divide\">|</span> Walk through lush rain forest, bamboo and past a giant banyan tree to Waimoku Falls, an incredible waterfall descending over a 400-foot wall of sheer lava rock <span class=\"divide\">|</span> Rise and shine with a morning yoga session at Travaasa Hana resort <span class=\"divide\">|</span> Taste decadent cacao at a historic Hawaiian plantation <span class=\"divide\">|</span> Soar over paradise on a scenic flight to lively Kahului.',3),(1803958,NULL,'3-4','','Walk in the footsteps of world-renowned painter Georgia O’Keeffe as we visit her beloved Ghost Ranch, a remote location where she found fifty years of inspiration| Hike up to Chimney Rock for a fantastic view of the Piedra Lumbre basin | Balance your hiking adventure with a yoga session | Visit the expansive and otherworldly Plaza Blanca (White Place), a dramatic geologic formation in the Rio Chama hills featured in a series of paintings by the artist | Unwind in our secluded sanctuary in the heart of Taos, an eco-resort surrounded by towering cottonwood trees | Marvel at millennia-old Taos Pueblo, the largest of New Mexico’s pre-Hispanic settlements and a World Heritage site.',1),(1803959,NULL,'','','',2),(1803960,NULL,'','','',3),(1804652,3271,'1-2','','Pedal through the heart of Central Oregon beside the mighty Deschutes River <span class=\"divide\">|</span> Cruise into Bend, the state&#39;s adventure capital, then park your bike and see what&#39;s on tap at a local craft brewery <span class=\"divide\">|</span> Hike in Oregon&#39;s rugged high-desert wonderland of sagebrush and rock spires <span class=\"divide\">|</span> At Smith Rock State Park, follow a trail alongside the Crooked River or ascend Misery Ridge for closer views of colorful Red Wall and Monkey Face, popular among rock climbers <span class=\"divide\">|</span> Spend a leisurely afternoon in downtown Bend perusing shops and galleries or joining a guided heritage tour. &nbsp;<br>',1),(1804653,3271,'3-4','','Spin into Deschutes National Forest on a locals&#39; favorite ride, where glistening alpine lakes share the expansive high desert with forests of pine, fir and hemlock <span class=\"divide\">|</span> Enjoy lunch with dramatic views of Mount Bachelor <span class=\"divide\">|</span> Meander along a riverside trail, watching placid waters transform into dramatic waterfalls <span class=\"divide\">|</span> Raft through Class II&ndash;III rapids as the Deschutes winds through lush woodland. &nbsp;<br>',2),(1804654,3271,'5-6','','Welcome to Crater Lake National Park&mdash;ready to ride the iconic Rim Drive? <span class=\"divide\">|</span> As you circle the rim of this enormous caldera, admire the lake&rsquo;s intense sapphire color and amazing clarity <span class=\"divide\">|</span> Each curve in the road brings another incredible vista, from the cinder cone of Wizard Island to the 9,000-foot peak of Mount Scott <span class=\"divide\">|</span> Unwind at the lodge or explore the spectacular landscape on foot <span class=\"divide\">|</span> Hike up Garfield Peak for a stunning bird&#39;s-eye-view of the lake and its surrounds. &nbsp;<br>',3),(1804862,NULL,'1-2','','Hike along a winding path through piñon and juniper forests in the foothills of the Sangre de Cristo Mountains | Explore the historic center of Santa Fe, the nation’s oldest capital city, to learn about its unique blend of Anglo, Spanish and Native cultures | A local expert guides us to noteworthy architectural landmarks including the Santa Fe Plaza and San Miguel Mission, reputedly the oldest church in the United States | Unroll your yoga mat and find your flow | Check out contemporary Southwest art, including a private collection at our hotel | Explore on foot the rugged canyon and mesa country of Bandelier National Monument, where we encounter a number of Ancestral Pueblo cliff dwellings.',1),(1804863,NULL,'5-6','','Hike up to a lookout point in a gorgeous conifer forest where you can soak up the wild landscape | Visit the historic village of Chimayó, home of a revered church to which devout pilgrims travel from great distances, seeking the healing powers of the sacred earth | End this fantastic week with a yoga class, a calm stroll amid volcanic tuff or a leisurely morning at our luxurious hotel. ',2),(1804864,NULL,'','','',3),(1805776,3208,'1-2','','Start your island journey by foot on the tropical foliage-laden flanks of the Makaleha Mountains <span class=\"divide\">|</span> Learn the ins and outs of artisan chocolate production while visiting a family-run farm in the eastern highlands <span class=\"divide\">|</span> Discover Hanalei\'s stunning landscape of waterfalls, emerald pinnacles and peaks, and one of the planet\'s most picturesque bays <span class=\"divide\">|</span> Fore! Youngsters tee off amid tropical gardens during a round of island mini-golf <span class=\"divide\">|</span> Find bliss at our luxurious getaway in Princeville.',1),(1805777,3208,'3','','Slip your sturdy sea kayak into the calm waters in Hanalei, keeping your eyes peeled for wildlife as you glide over the water <span class=\"divide\">|</span> Enjoy <i>ono grindz</i>&mdash;fresh and tasty local island fare&mdash;washed down with a tropical fruit smoothie <span class=\"divide\">|</span> A scenic journey along the Coconut Coast delivers you to Kauai\'s sunshine-drenched southern shore <span class=\"divide\">|</span> Grab a mask and snorkel to get acquainted with the colorful creatures just offshore <span class=\"divide\">|</span> Splash around on Poipu\'s postcard-perfect sandy beaches. ',2),(1805778,3208,'4-5','','Stand in awe of colorful Waimea Canyon, known as the Grand Canyon of the Pacific <span class=\"divide\">|</span> Hit the trail in Kokee State Park to an overlook above the Awaawapuhi and Nualolo Valleys <span class=\"divide\">|</span> Libation in hand, watch the sun sink below the horizon from our oceanfront hotel in Poipu <span class=\"divide\">|</span> Discover a spectacular rugged coastline while hiking the Mahaulepu Heritage Trail past lithified sand dunes and craggy sea stacks.',3),(1805815,3206,'1-2','','Start your island journey by foot in a tropical jungle on the flanks of the Makaleha Mountains <span class=\"divide\">|</span> Learn the ins and outs of artisan tea production while visiting a family-run farm <span class=\"divide\">|</span> Sample locally harvested fare, including taro, <i>ulu</i> (breadfruit) and coconut candy <span class=\"divide\">|</span> Discover Hanalei\'s stunning landscape of waterfalls, emerald pinnacles and peaks, and one of the planet\'s most picturesque bays <span class=\"divide\">|</span> Slip your sturdy sea kayak into Hanalei\'s calm waters, keeping your eyes peeled for wildlife as you paddle <span class=\"divide\">|</span> Find bliss in paradise at our luxurious getaway in Princeville.',1),(1805816,3206,'3','','Experience life in the clouds at the base of Mount Wai\'aleale, said to be one of the wettest places on earth <span class=\"divide\">|</span> Hike past African tulips, lush ferns and grasses used for making the Hawaii\'s signature hula skirts <span class=\"divide\">|</span> A scenic journey along the Coconut Coast delivers you to Kauai\'s sunshine-drenched southern shore <span class=\"divide\">|</span> Grab a mask and snorkel to get acquainted with the colorful creatures just offshore <span class=\"divide\">|</span> Splash around on Poipu\'s postcard-perfect sandy beaches.',2),(1805817,3206,'4-5','','Stand in awe of colorful Waimea Canyon, known as the Grand Canyon of the Pacific <span class=\"divide\">|</span> Hit the trail in Kokee State Park to an overlook above the Awaawapuhi and Nualolo Valleys <span class=\"divide\">|</span> Libation in hand, watch the sun sink below the horizon from our oceanfront hotel in Poipu <span class=\"divide\">|</span> Discover a spectacular rugged coastline while hiking the Mahaulepu Heritage Trail past lithified sand dunes and craggy sea stacks.',3),(1808025,NULL,'1-2','','Visit a coffee farm and discover the story behind Kona\'s gourmet crop <span class=\"divide\">|</span> Hike along the coast where Hawaii\'s best scenery is on display&mdash;sweeping ocean vistas, beautiful valleys, lush tropical gardens and dramatic cliffs <span class=\"divide\">|</span> Visit Puuhonua o Honaunau National Historical Park, an ancient place of refuge and a sacred healing ground for locals today <span class=\"divide\">|</span> Stargaze as you soak in a hot tub at our charming bed-and-breakfast <span class=\"divide\">|</span> Salute the sun and flow through your yoga practice in a guided class <span class=\"divide\">|</span> Explore a newly formed caldera with a local guide and walk through a lush forest in Hawaii Volcanoes National Park, taking in the beauty of Kilauea, one of the most active volcanoes on Earth <span class=\"divide\">|</span> Spin past giant tree ferns on Crater Rim Drive and discover Mauna Ulu, the growing mountain.\"',1),(1808026,NULL,'3-6','','Greet the day with a beachside yoga class <span class=\"divide\">|</span> Bike the Hamakua Coast, some of the Big Island\'s most scenic riding <span class=\"divide\">|</span> &#8203;Kayak past rocky cliffs and secluded sea caves in the crystal-clear waters around Puako <span class=\"divide\">|</span> Snorkel among colorful parrotfish, Moorish idols and Hawaiian lionfish <span class=\"divide\">|</span> At our oceanfront retreat, swim, find your balance on a stand-up paddleboard or bliss out on the hotel\'s half-moon beach <span class=\"divide\">|</span> &#8203;Start the day with a sunrise paddle in a traditional outrigger canoe <span class=\"divide\">|</span> Spin along the sun-soaked Kohala Coast, tracing 30 miles of the Kona Ironman Triathlon\'s cycling course <span class=\"divide\">|</span> Learn about historic petroglyphs and King Kamehameha the Great on a coastal walk. ',2),(1808092,NULL,'1-2','','Experience a fascinating convergence of Thai, Laotian, Burmese and Chinese cultures <span class=\"divide\">|</span> Salute the sun in a morning yoga class <span class=\"divide\">|</span> Receive a blessing from the village elders and visit with the resident monk <span class=\"divide\">|</span> Spin into the countryside past thriving rice and garlic fields and stands of papaya and teak <span class=\"divide\">|</span> Learn from a local gardener how to plant and harvest rice <span class=\"divide\">|</span> Get a behind-the-scenes look at how traditional Thai dishes are prepared.',1),(1808093,NULL,'3-4','','Curious locals welcome you as you bike picturesque rural roads through remote villages <span class=\"divide\">|</span> Beneath the white Buddha, offer alms to monks at sunrise <span class=\"divide\">|</span> A scenic descent leads to the trading center of Fang and temple-rich Thaton <span class=\"divide\">|</span> Start the day on your mat with a morning yoga session <span class=\"divide\">|</span> Learn about the Shan people, originally from China and Burma <span class=\"divide\">|</span> Put your culinary skills to the test during a cooking class, then taste the fruits of your own labor <span class=\"divide\">|</span> Listen to a remarkable performance of a hill tribe choir.',2),(1808094,NULL,'5','','Float in longtail boats down the Maekok River <span class=\"divide\">|</span> Ride through a peaceful village-dotted landscape into vibrant Chiang Rai <span class=\"divide\">|</span> Embark on a culinary adventure as you wander the streets of Chiang Rai and sample some of Thailand\'s unique delicacies and delicious street food.',3),(1808095,NULL,'6-8','','Rise early to salute the sun with gentle yoga stretches <span class=\"divide\">|</span> Bike alongside the Mekong River on the Laos and Myanmar border, passing tobacco fields and rice paddies on the way to the ancient Burmese kingdom of Chiang Saen <span class=\"divide\">|</span> Spin to the spectacular Chom Kitti temple <span class=\"divide\">|</span> Learn about the area\'s history of the lucrative opium trade, a commodity worth its weight in gold <span class=\"divide\">|</span> Browse Sop Ruak\'s market for a refreshing Thai iced tea and one-of-a-kind handicrafts.',4),(1808690,3385,'1-2','','Moët & Chandon, Veuve Clicquot and other celebrated vineyards provide an idyllic backdrop as you cycle in the Coteaux de Champagn <span class=\"divide\">|</span> Explore a World Heritage landscape just outside of Paris <span class=\"divide\">|</span> Visit Abbaye d\'Hautvillers, resting place of monk Dom Pierre Pérignon <span class=\"divide\">|</span> Marvel at the splendid properties of prestigious<i> négociants </i>(wine merchants) on the Avenue de Champagne <span class=\"divide\">|</span> At Moët & Chandon\'s legendary property, an exclusive cellar tour and dinner await.',1),(1808691,3385,'3','','Starting in the charming town of Marlenheim, spin along the Route des Vins (Wine Route), beloved for its lovely canals and picturesque villages <span class=\"divide\">|</span> Skirt the graceful Vosges foothills and bike easygoing terrain through the heart of Alsace <span class=\"divide\">|</span> Decorated with Alsatian-style half-timbered houses and window boxes of geraniums, Obernai is a heavenly place to explore on foot.',2),(1808692,3385,'4-6','','Wander through Château du Haut-Koenigsbourg, a 12th-century fortress overlooking the Rhine River Valley <span class=\"divide\">|</span> Discover beautifully preserved Riquewihr and Eguisheim, both among the designated Most Beautiful Villages of France, with stunning Gothic churches and medieval fortifications <span class=\"divide\">|</span> Savor an incredible meal at Auberge de l\'Ill, an exceptional family-run restaurant that has been awarded at least two Michelin stars for 50 years and counting <span class=\"divide\">|</span> Take in views of the Vosges Massif on one side and Germany on the other during one last morning ride in the valley.',3),(1808937,3333,'1','','At the heart of the Colorado Plateau lies Utah\'s spectacular canyon country <span class=\"divide\">|</span> Pedal through a landscape of orange and white Navajo sandstone cliffs, a place the early Mormon pioneers called Snow Canyon.<br><br> ',1),(1808938,3333,'2-3','','Experience awe-inspiring Cedar Breaks National Monument, a lesser-known gem with stone towers, canyons, columns and arches <span class=\"divide\">|</span> Descend into meadows ringed by quaking aspen and ponderosa pine <span class=\"divide\">|</span> Spin across the high desert to Bryce Canyon, where visibility on a clear day exceeds 100 miles <span class=\"divide\">|</span> Explore an otherworldly wonderland during a ride to Rainbow Point <span class=\"divide\">|</span> Hike on aptly named trails such as Sunrise, Inspiration and Queen\'s Garden for a new perspective amid the area\'s famous hoodoos <span class=\"divide\">|</span> Grab your camera and a seat on the canyon rim to watch the sun set&mdash;an unforgettable performance.<br>',2),(1808939,3333,'4-6','','Witness extraordinary rock formations en route to Zion as you pedal through Red Canyon, brimming with crimson-colored pinnacles, spires and more hoodoos <span class=\"divide\">|</span> Watch for the impressive white-sandstone Elkhart Cliffs and geometric Checkerboard Mesa <span class=\"divide\">|</span> Cool off with a dip in the pool or relax in a steaming hot tub at our hotel near the Virgin River <span class=\"divide\">|</span> Picturesque routes abound in this hiker\'s paradise from easy walks past emerald pools to unforgettable climbs providing panoramas of Zion\'s soaring sandstone <span class=\"divide\">|</span> Enjoy a quiet morning ride through stunning (and car-free!) Zion Canyon to end your biking adventure. <br> ',3);
