es/trips/MYCI-yucatan-multiadventure-tour-1.jpg'),(3237,'Bryce & Capitol Reef Multi-Adventure Tour - Older Teens & 20s','Utah&#39;s Hidden National Parks & Monuments',0,'St. George, Utah','St. George, Utah','The terrain on this trip includes a mix of well-maintained dirt trails and paved walkways, with some exposed ridgetop and narrow canyon sections.','Take a journey along the road less traveled through a kaleidoscope of remote and magnificent landscapes in Utah&rsquo;s stunning canyon country. Find solitude and adventure as you explore the bizarre, wild and wonderful terrain of rock spires, domes, arches, slot canyons and a giant wrinkle in the earth&rsquo;s surface that stretches for almost 100 miles. This natural showcase of wonders must be seen to be believed!','','https://s3.us-west-1.amazonaws.com/professor.raupach/acme_travel/images/maps/MBGQ_15_map_sm.jpg','https://s3.us-west-1.amazonaws.com/professor.raupach/acme_travel/images/maps/20_MBYQB.jpg','Bryce Capital Reef Map','Bryce & Capitol Reef Family Multi-Adventure Tour','Bryce Zion Utah Map','Bryce & Capitol Reef Family Multi-Adventure Tour','<ul><li><strong>Journey</strong> within one of the most remote and surreal landscapes in the least-visited of Utah&rsquo;s Mighty Five national parks</li><li><strong>Pedal </strong>along the rim of Bryce Canyon, from one spectacular vista to the next, as you make your way by bike to Rainbow Point</li><li><strong>Travel</strong> through the sedimentary rock layers of Grand Staircase-Escalante National Monument between Bryce and Capitol Reef National Parks</li><li><strong>Hike</strong> into a valley filled with the world\'s highest concentration of hoodoos&mdash;totem pole-shaped rock spires&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</li></ul>','https://s3.us-west-1.amazonaws.com/professor.raupach/acme_travel/images/trips/MBYQB-canyons-multisport-1.jpg'),(3271,'Oregon\'s Cascades & Crater Lake Family Multi-Adventure Tour - Older Teens & 20s','Bend, the Cascades & the Deschutes River',0,'Bend, Oregon','Bend, Oregon','The terrain on this trip ranges from moderately rolling hills to steeper grades on the longer options. Routes vary from alpine forested paths to loose rocky trails. High altitude encountered in Crater Lake. Biking routes vary from quiet roads to highways with little shoulder. On early-summer trips encountering snow on the hiking trails is possible, which can pose additional challenges.','Hiking along lush forested river trails and biking down a scenic byway through the foothills of the Cascades. There&#39;s splashing and rafting on the rollicking Deschutes River. An overnight at the historic Crater Lake Lodge. \"It&#39;s so blue!\" Don&#39;t be surprised if you hear this uttered at least once. Because Crater Lake really is that blue and containing your excitement is no small task.&nbsp;<br>','','https://s3.us-west-1.amazonaws.com/professor.raupach/acme_travel/images/maps/BCKI_15_map_sm.jpg','https://s3.us-west-1.amazonaws.com/professor.raupach/acme_travel/images/maps/20_MCKIB.jpg','Oregon Crater Lake Map','Crater Lake Family Multi-Adventure Tour','Oregon Crater Lake Map','Oregon Cascades & Crater Lake Family Multi-Adventure Tour','&nbsp;<ul><li><strong>Embark</strong> on exhilarating routes amid ever-changing scenery in Central Oregon&#39;s rugged high country&nbsp;</li><li><strong>Hike </strong>the high-desert trails of Smith Rock for out-of-this-world views of the Cascade Mountains&nbsp;</li><li><strong>Explore</strong> Bend, Oregon&#39;s adventure playground with more breweries per capita than anywhere else in the state&nbsp;</li><li><strong>Bike</strong> the rim of Crater Lake&#39;s world-famous caldera&mdash;one of the most spectacular rides in America&nbsp;&nbsp;</li></ul>&nbsp;','https://s3.us-west-1.amazonaws.com/professor.raupach/acme_travel/images/trips/MCKI-crater-lake-multi-adventure-tour-1.jpg'),(3333,'Bryce & Zion Family Bike Tour - Older Teens & 20s','Red-Rock Wonders in Utah\'s National Parks',0,'St. George, Utah','St. George, 